ies, with studies consistently identifying traffic as dominant NOx source in urban areas\n\n## Data Source (may not be directly accessible)\n- **Name**: International Organization of Motor Vehicle Manufacturers\n- **Organization**: OICA\n- **URL**: not provided\n- **Format**: Excel\n- **Accessibility**: restricted\n- **Coverage**: Global vehicle ownership statistics by country\n\n\n## References\n- https://electroiq.com/stats/car-ownership-statistics/\n- https://theicct.org/stack/vehicle-nox-emissions-the-basics/\n\n## EPI Target Data Summary\n**Target Indicator**: OEB — Mean annual exposure to ozone across a country\'s Key Biodiversity Areas\n**Units**: ppm\n**Polarity**: negative\n**Source**: Copernicus/Bird Life\n**Data File**: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/OEB_raw.csv`\n**Coverage**: 213 countries, 2003-2022 (4260 observations)\n**Summary Stats**: mean=0.07, std=0.02, median=0.07\n\n**Control Variable Files**:\n- GPC: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/GPC_raw.csv`\n- POP: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/POP_raw.csv`\n- URB: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/URB_raw.csv`\n\n## Caveats to Consider\n- Vehicle ownership is lagging indicator of actual emissions\n- Fleet composition and emission standards vary dramatically\n- Relationship breaks down where vehicle emissions are not dominant source\n\n## Output Directory\nWrite ALL output files to: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/outputs/OEB/stage2/OEB-H06/`\n- `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/outputs/OEB/stage2/OEB-H06/verify.py` — your analysis script\n- `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/outputs/OEB/stage2/OEB-H06/result.json` — the structured results\n\n## Data Discovery Strategy (try ALL 4 approaches before giving up)\n\n### Approach 1: Direct URL Fetch\nIf a URL is provided above, use `requests.get()` to download the data.\nParse whatever format you get (CSV, Excel, JSON